first dictionary \"definitions\" has the form: **name (str) -> Definition**, containing an\nobject of each field in the SDDS file (of type `Parameter`, `Array` or `Column`). The \"values\"\ndictionary has the form: **name (str) -> value**. To access them: `sdds_file = SddsFile(...)`.\n\n```python\ndef_ = sdds_file.definitions[\"name\"]\nval = sdds_file.values[\"name\"]\n# The definitions and values can also be accessed like:\ndef_, val = sdds_file[\"name\"]\n```\n\nArgs:\n\n: version (str): Always needs to be \"SDDS1\"!\n  description (Description): Optional. Description Tag.\n  definitions_list (list[Definition]): List of definitions objects,\n\n  > describing the data.\n\n  values_list (list[Any]): List of values for the SDDS data.\n\n  : Same lengths as definitions.\n\nFields:\n\n: version (str): Always needs to be \"SDDS1\"!\n  description (Description): Optional. Description Tag.\n  definitions (dict[str, Definition]): Definitions of the data, mapped to their name.\n  values (dict[str, Any]): Values of the data, mapped to their name.\n"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "sdds.writer", "documentation": ["# Writer\n\nThis module contains the writing functionality of `sdds`.\nIt provides a high-level function to write SDDS files in different formats, and a series of helpers.\n"], "functions": [{"name": "sdds.writer.write_sdds", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "sdds_file", "type": {"name": "SddsFile", "xref": {"fqname": "sdds.classes.SddsFile", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "output_path", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "pathlib.Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Writes SddsFile