 {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "opener", "type": {"name": "OpenerType", "xref": {"fqname": "OpenerType", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "SddsFile", "xref": {"fqname": "sdds.classes.SddsFile", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Reads an SDDS file from the specified `file_path`.\n\nArgs:\n: file_path (Union[pathlib.Path, str]): `Path` object to the input SDDS file. Can be a\n\n  : `string`, in which case it will be cast to a `Path` object.\n\n  endianness (str): Endianness of the file, either 'big' or 'little'. If not given,\n\n  : the endianness is either extracted from the comments in the header of the file\n    (if present) or determined by the machine you are running on. Binary files\n    written by this package are all big-endian, and contain a comment in the file.\n\n  opener (OpenerType): Callable to open the SDDS file. Uses `open(file, mode=\"rb\")` by\n\n  : default. One can use provided openers for specific format or bring their own, see\n    the examples below.\n\nReturns:\n\n: An `SddsFile` object containing the loaded data.\n\nExamples:\n\n> To read a typical file, one can use the default options:\n>\n> ```python\n> import sdds\n>\n> data = sdds.read(\"some/location/to/file.sdds\")\n> ```\n>\n> To read a `gzip`-compressed file, use the provided opener function:\n>\n> ```python\n> import sdds\n> from sdds.reader import gzip_open\n>\n> data = sdds.read(\"some/location/to/file.sdds.gz\", opener=gzip_open)\n> ```\n>\n> To read another specific compression format, bring your own opener abstraction.\n> It should take a single parameter for the path-like object pointing to the file,\n> and return a context manager providing byte-data of the file. For instance the\n> `gzip_opener` from the example above is built as `functools.partial(gzip.open, mode=\"rb\")`.\n>\n> ```python\n> import sdds\n> from functools import partial\n> from relevant_module import opening_function\n>\n> your_opener = partial(opening_function, some_option)\n> data = sdds.read(\"some/location/to/file.sdds.extension\", opener=your_opener)\n> ```\n", "----- Reader Function ----- #"]}, {"name": "sdds.reader._read_header", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "inbytes", "type": {"name": "IO", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.IO", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Definition", "xref": {"fqname": "sdds.classes.Definition", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Description", "xref": {"fqname": "sdds.classes.Description", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "Data", "xref": {"fqname": "sdds.classes.Data", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["#############################################################################", "Common reading of header and data.", "#############################################################################"]}, {"name": "sdds.reader._sort_definitions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "orig_defs", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Definition", "xref": {"fqname": "sdds.classes.Definition", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Definition", "xref": {"fqname": "sdds.classes.Definition", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Sorts the definitions in the parameter, array, 